@xlucas I saw some funny behaviour doing this as well on a non docker.io repository.  I capture the http requests and the manifest list json looked something like this:

```
{
   "schemaVersion":2,
   "manifests":[
      {
         "mediaType":"application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json",
         "digest":"sha256:e9818a25b9c9aa2bfaabd4459ae8baa4c4f02e392cb835a5d8895a2f00bc53c1",
         "size":749,
         "platform":{
            "architecture":"amd64",
            "os":"linux"
         }
      },
      {
         "mediaType":"application/vnd.docker.distribution.manifest.v2+json",
         "digest":"sha256:8cc2a397a9e7dd4e2cef626bad3066e3e8c552a665f09547d3aab52f5b902772",
         "size":749,
         "platform":{
            "architecture":"arm64",
            "os":"linux"
         }
      }
   ]
}
```

Which is missing the `mediaType` for the manifest list itself which I do not believe is valid.  I found this intermediate step produced the correct manifest list.

```
docker buildx build --platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64  -o type=oci,dest=- . > myimage-oci.tar
skopeo  copy  oci-archive:myimage-oci.tar dir:tmp -f v2s2 --all
skopeo  copy  --dest-tls-verify=false --dest-creds=username:password dir:tmp docker://localhost:8081/docker-local/hello --all
```
I will dig in and see what is going on here with the missing mediaType, but I would be curious if this solves the problem for you with docker.io
